<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<exercise xmlns="https://spatext.clontz.org" version="0.2">
    <statement>
        <p>
Assume we are considering the set-theoretic universe of
the first ten lowercase English letters
<m>\mathcal{U} = \{a,b,\dots,j\}</m>, and
let <m>X=\{ {{X}} \}</m> and <m>Y = \{ {{Y}} \}</m>.
        </p>
        <p>
Explain and demonstrate how to find each of the following
(using symbolic notation, e.g. <m>\cup,\cap,\dots</m>).
        </p>
    </statement>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
The cardinalities of <m>X</m> and <m>Y</m>.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
<m>|X| = {{Xcard}}</m> and <m>|Y| = {{Ycard}}</m>.
            </p>
        </answer>
    </task>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
The Venn diagram representation of <m>X</m> and <m>Y</m>
in this universe.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
(illustration not provided)
            </p>
        </answer>
    </task>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
The union of <m>X</m> and <m>Y</m>.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
<m>X\cup Y = \{ {{union}} \}</m>.
            </p>
        </answer>
    </task>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
The intersection of <m>X</m> and <m>Y</m>.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
<m>X\cap Y = \{ {{intersection}} \}</m>.
            </p>
        </answer>
    </task>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
The complement of <m>{{complement_set}}</m>.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
<m>\overline{ {{complement_set}} } =
\mathcal{U} \setminus {{complement_set}} =
\mathcal{U} - {{complement_set}} = \{ {{complement}} \}</m>.
            </p>
        </answer>
    </task>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
The difference of <m>{{difference_first}}</m> and <m>{{difference_second}}</m>.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
<m>{{difference_first}} \setminus {{difference_second}} =
{{difference_first}} - {{difference_second}} = \{ {{difference}} \}</m>.
            </p>
        </answer>
    </task>
</exercise>